item.title: Barry Gibb
item.description: Sir Barry Alan Crompton Gibb is a musician, singer-songwriter and record producer who rose to worldwide fame as a co-founder of the group Bee Gees, one of the most commercially successful groups in the history of popular music. With his younger brothers, twins Robin and Maurice Gibb, he formed a songwriting partnership beginning in 1955. He has lived and worked in Britain, Australia, and the United States, currently holding dual UK–US citizenship.
